cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  Reproducibility code for AI-enhanced calibration of IoT particulate matter
  sensors in open-pit mining
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite both this code and the underlying
  manuscript (see "preferred-citation" below).
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Marwa
    family-names: Amara
    affiliation: >-
      Faculty of Computing and Information Technology, Northern Border
      University, Arar, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia
    email: Marwa.amara@nbu.edu.sa
# A Zenodo DOI will be added here once the v1.0.x release is archived
# (see UPLOAD_GUIDE.md, Step 6).
repository-code: 'https://github.com/marwaamara/iot-pm-mining-calibration'
abstract: >-
  Python implementation of an AI-enhanced calibration pipeline for low-cost
  IoT particulate matter sensors (Plantower PMS5003 class) deployed in
  open-pit mining environments, including a JCGM-101-compliant uncertainty
  budget combining out-of-fold residuals, Monte-Carlo input propagation,
  and bias correction. Validated on the KAPSARC Riyadh reference dataset
  (semi-synthetic) and the Kelly et al. 2023 Salt Lake Valley dust-event
  dataset (real co-located PMS5003 + FEM measurements).
keywords:
  - particulate matter
  - low-cost sensor calibration
  - measurement uncertainty
  - JCGM 101
  - Monte Carlo
  - machine learning
  - open-pit mining
  - PMS5003
license: MIT
